   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR THE SECRET OF BUILDING OUTLINE Something critical to the accomplishment of God s eternal economy: To be built up with the fellow believers is the Lord s supreme and highest requirement to His faithful seekers according to one of the divine attributes, the divine oneness, of the Divine Trinity John 17.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Being built up with the fellow partakers of the divine life is the highest virtue of the one who pursues after Christ in God s eternal economy.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Not one of the descendants of the fallen Adamic race has the capacity and ability to meet the high requirements of the kingdom of the heavens.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Only the regenerated, sanctified, renewed, and transformed believers are qualified to fulfill the supreme requirements of the kingdom of the heavens.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The God-men, who have the divine life, the divine nature, and the divine mind, and who participate in the divinity of God, have the divine capacity to carry out the divine requirements of the divine kingdom.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The secret of building the sixth section of God s organic salvation: The prerequisites of the believers building up in the church, the Body of Christ: To realize that the Lord loves and wants to have a built church, not scattered individual believers.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To acknowledge that all the believers have been baptized in one Spirit into one Body and that God has placed the members in the Body and blended all the Body together 1 Cor 12:13a, 18, 24.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To be in harmony with the fellow believers and to be in one accord with the Body in prayer, which issues in the establishment of the church Matt 18:19; Acts 1:14.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To practice the oneness of the Divine Trinity in the Divine Trinity as the Divine Trinity does John 17:21-23: By the divine life with its source, the divine name of the Father vv.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>2-3, 6, 26.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>By the divine word as the truth that sanctifies the believers from the world vv.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>14-19.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>By the divine glory the divine sonship with the Father s life and nature as the divine right to express the Father vv.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>22, 24.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>To keep the oneness of the Spirit diligently Eph 4:3: In the constitution of the Body with the Divine Trinity as the source, the element, and the essence vv.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>4-6.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Through the perfection by the gifted members for the building up of the Body of Christ vv.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>By the growth in the divine life, growing into the Head in all things vv.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>13, 15.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>To be in the common fellowship of the enjoyment of Christ as the believers common portion for the keeping of the oneness of the Body to witness that Christ is neither divisible nor divided 1 Cor 1:2, 9-13.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>To have the common fellowship in the spirit and to have the common thinking and common love in one spirit, with one soul, and on one common standing for the testimony of the oneness of the Body of Christ Phil 2:1-2; 1:27.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>To live and walk by the Spirit Gal 5:16, 25 and walk according to the mingled spirit Rom 8:4 , setting our mind on the mingled spirit, being indwelt by the pneumatic Christ, the indwelling Spirit, to impart life within us and for us to put to death the practices of the body Rom 8:4, 6, 9-13.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>To be conformed to the death of Christ, to have the self, natural man, flesh, distorted disposition, peculiarities, personal preference and tastes, etc., all crucified with Christ by the power of the resurrection of Christ Phil 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>To magnify Christ through living Him by the bountiful supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ Phil 1:19-21.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>To minister Christ, dispensing Him, to all contacts.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>To discern the spirit, which is of power, love, and sobermindedness, from the soul Heb 4:12; 2 Tim 1:7.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The builders of the divine building: Christ the Head, who speaks the words of God, imparts the divine life and gives the Spirit without measure Matt 16:18; John 3:34.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The gifted persons, especially the apostles and the prophets, perfect the saints for the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The perfected saints share the burden of the perfecting, gifted persons.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>The entire Body Eph 4:16: Through every joint of the rich supply.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Through the operation in the measure of each one part.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>By the growth of the Body unto the building up of itself in love.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Christ makes His home in the hearts of the saints through the strengthening with power through the Spirit into their inner man unto the fullness of the Triune God for His expression Eph 3:16-19.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The Triune God builds the abodes in the Father s house through the Spirit remaining within the lover of Christ, and the Father and the Son visit the lover of Christ to make the mutual abode John 14:23.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>The foundation of the divine building: The redeeming and saving Christ 1 Cor 3:11.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>The apostles and the prophets with their revelation received of Christ as the rock and their teaching Eph 2:20; Matt 16:18; Acts 2:42; 1 Tim 1:4.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>The materials of the divine building: The Divine Trinity as the transformed precious items gold, silver, and precious stones 1 Cor 3:12: Gold, signifying God the Father as the base of the divine building Gen 2:11; Rev 21:18b, 21b.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Silver or bdellium and pearl, signifying Christ in His redeeming and life-releasing death and His life-dispensing resurrection Gen 2:12; Rev 21:21a.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Precious stones, signifying the Spirit in His transforming and building work Gen 2:12; Rev 21:19-20.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>The transformed believers who are the divine plants transformed into the divine minerals 1 Cor 3:6-9.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Wood, in contrast to gold, signifies the nature of the natural man; grass, in contrast to silver, signifies the fallen man, the man of the flesh 1 Pet 1:24 ; and stubble, in contrast to precious stones, signifies the work and living that issue from an earthen source: all these are not worthy to be used as materials for the divine building 1 Cor 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>The work of the divine building: Renewing issues in transformation, and transformation issues in building up; the building up of the jasper wall of the New Jerusalem goes along with its transformation Rev 21:18a.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>It is the believers growth in the divine life and their being joined together in the divine life Eph 4:15-16; 2:21.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>It is the believers being built together in Christ into a dwelling of God by the Spirit in their spirit possessed by Christ, both of which are mingled as one spirit Eph 2:22.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>It is also by the Spirit s operation, distributing to each member different gifts for the building up of the Body 1 Cor 12:4, 7-11.</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>The building work with gold, silver, and precious stones will be rewarded by Christ at His coming back; if it is with wood, grass, and stubble, it will be burned on the day of the Lord s coming 1 Cor 3:12-14.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>The consummation of the divine building: The church in many localities as the house of God to be God s dwelling place, the holy temple in the Lord 1 Tim 3:15; Eph 2:21-22.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>The Body of Christ in the whole universe as the expression of Christ Eph 1:23: In fact, all the believers in Christ have been baptized into one Body by the Spirit 1 Cor 12:13a.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>In practicality, based on the fact, all the believers have to be built together into the Body of Christ Eph 4:12 by the builders of the divine building through the age of the New Testament.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>The destroyers of the divine building: Those who blow the wind of divisive teachings by stressing things other than the central teaching concerning God s economy Eph 4:14; 1 Tim 1:4.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>Those who preach and teach heresies 2 Pet 2:1; 2 John 7-11.</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>Those who are factious, sectarian Titus 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>Those who make divisions Rom 16:17.</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>Those who are ambitious for position 3 John 9.</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>Those who are wolves, not sparing the flock Acts 20:29.</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>Those who speak perverted things to draw away the believers after them Acts 20:30.</S>
   </TEXT>
